From: Nick Piggin <npiggin@suse.de>
Subject: [patch 5/9] mm: lockless probe

Probing pages and radix_tree_tagged are lockless operations with the
lockless radix-tree. Convert these users to RCU locking rather than
using tree_lock.

Signed-off-by: Nick Piggin <npiggin@suse.de>

---
 mm/readahead.c |    4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

Index: linux-2.6.24-rt1/mm/readahead.c
===================================================================
--- linux-2.6.24-rt1.orig/mm/readahead.c	2008-01-25 15:06:29.000000000 -0500
+++ linux-2.6.24-rt1/mm/readahead.c	2008-01-25 15:08:05.000000000 -0500
@@ -376,9 +376,9 @@ ondemand_readahead(struct address_space 
 	if (hit_readahead_marker) {
 		pgoff_t start;
 
-		read_lock_irq(&mapping->tree_lock);
+		rcu_read_lock();
 		start = radix_tree_next_hole(&mapping->page_tree, offset, max+1);
-		read_unlock_irq(&mapping->tree_lock);
+		rcu_read_unlock();
 
 		if (!start || start - offset > max)
 			return 0;
